headline: Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q2 Earnings
summary: Professional tools and equipment manufacturer Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales falling 7.9% year on year to $1.18 billion. Its GAAP profit of $4.72 per share was 2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
